This will just keep a clue for how to do the basic configuration of pycharm for python development

# jinja2 autocomplete
	1. create a templates folder
	2. right-click on the templates folder
	3. move to "Mark Directory as" on the dropdown menu
	4. select "Template Folder" option from "Mark Directory as" menu
	5. choose "jinja2" as the template for "Python language templates"
